HEADWORD: Jambolana
<hw>Jam`bo*la"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Pg.
<ets>jambol⟦atil⟧o</ets> a kind of tropical fruit.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A myrtaceous tree of the West Indies and tropical
America (<spn>Calyptranthes Jambolana</spn>), with astringent bark, used
for dyeing. It bears an edible fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

